The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Italy thrash Portugal; Spain win
                                                Italy thrash Portugal; Spain win
                      
	London: Germany, Italy and the Netherlands continued their preparations for this years European Championship by winning friendly internationals Wednesday.         
	Germany won 3-0 in Austria, who are set to co-host the June 7-29 competition with Switzerland, while Italy beat Portugal 3-1 and the Netherlands defeated hosts Croatia 3-0 on goals by Johnny Heitinga, Klaus-Jan Huntelaar and Jan Vennegoor of Hesselink.         
	Defending European champion Greece also won, beating Finland 2-1, while Poland surprised the Czech Republic 2-0 and Spain beat France 1-0.         
	With Romania losing at Israel 0-1 and Sweden drawing 0-0 at Turkey, Russia were the only one of the 16 teams set to contest the European Championship who were not in action.         
	Record three-time European champions Germany won in Vienna on second-half goals by Thomas Hitzlsperger, Miroslav Klose and substitute Mario Gomez.         
	Austria and Germany meet each other again in the final group B match at Viennas Ernst Happel Stadium on June 16. Poland and Croatia are the other teams in that group.         
	Poland beat the Czechs on first-half goals by Wojciech Lobodzinski and Mariusz Lewandowski, while the Netherlands eased past Croatia in Split even through it was missing Ruud van Nistelrooy, Arjen Robben, Robin van Persie and Clarence Seedorf.         
	Heitinga scored in the ninth minute with a low header from Wesley Sneijders free kick, and Darijo Srna missed a chance for the hosts before Huntelaar tapped in to make it 2-0 in the 37th. (AP)                                                                                                                        
